column5: I have been on Chemong Lake for the past 10 years and know the fishing quite well in the area but  have an opportunity to buy a property in Woodville on Julian Lake.  Does anyone have any expert or first hand knowledge of the fishing in that particular lake other than it is land-locked and the size of a bath tub?
The lake has Small Mouth and a few Musky...
Looks like a pretty small lake, my buddy and I were on Big Cedar last Thursday and drove past Julian lake on the way.  Big Cedar has bass & musky, so I assume Julian would be the same.
